The paper deals with network traffic reduction techniques and their implementation in network nodes. This falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses routing and memory placement problems in the network, which can be categorized under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also deals with redundancy elimination, which is a security concern and can be categorized under cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the benefits of network compression on scale-free networks, which can be categorized under social and information networks (cs.SI).
